-- Indian shares slump tracking weak global markets; Infosys surges
-- By Indulal PM
-- Fri Oct 10, 2014 06:08AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Oct 10 (Reuters) - Indian shares posted their biggest fall in 2-1/2 weeks on Friday, as blue-chips continued to be hit by concerns that weaker global markets would dent demand from foreign investors, although software firm Infosys Ltd surged after a profit beat.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally closed 1.21  percent lower at 26,315.44 points, while the broader NSE index <.NSEI> fell 1.22 percent to 7,863.75.